Description for the new reaction algorythm: 1: Each reaction gets a new object (reactionX).
- id: Identifier - only for logging relevant
- text: The displayed message on the screen
- messageRows: Used to determine the height of the textbox
- textboxBackground: Used to control the kind of background of the message window
- reactionPictureOptions: Contains the strings of all possible reation pics inside this list
2: reactionTextOptions.push(reactionX, ...) => Adds all reactions into the reactionTextOptions-list
3: categoryId = Math.floor(Math.random() * reactionTextOptions.length) => RNG to randomly select one of the reactions by array position
4: categoryObject = reactionTextOptions[categoryId] => Extract categoryObject out of list by selected categoryId
5: Calling relevant variables out of the selected object
